      "question": "To draw a pair of tangents to a circle which are inclined to each other at an angle of $60^{\\circ}$, it is required to draw tangents at the endpoints of those two radii of the circle, the angle between which is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The angle between the tangents and the angle between the radii at the points of contact are supplementary.",
          "Let the angle between the radii be $\\theta$.",
          "$\\theta + 60^{\\circ} = 180^{\\circ}$",
          "$\\theta = 120^{\\circ}$"
        ],
        "derivation": "\\theta = 180^{\\circ} - 60^{\\circ} = 120^{\\circ}"
